content.description: The chossy trail-facing side of The Chunk Boulder offers a handful of toprope-able lines. This route (the path of least resistance) begins in the center of the face and travels diagonally to the right toward the arete.
content.location: Center of the trail-facing (South?) side The Chunk Boulder.

content.description: Start sitting on left hand edge and right hand crimp directly under the crack feature. Use the crack to hit the lip and traverse left to NE corner to top out. Be careful with the dusty flake. Please don't intentionally destroy.
content.location: NE Corner of the Chunk. Starts under the roof and ends at NE Corner after lip traverse.

content.description: Start on ledge below crack and to the left. Work up the crack half way then move left to sloper and further out left to rail on the arete. Once you hit rail on arete move up to top out on arete
content.location: Start next to medicine man and move up same crack until half way to traverse left on sloper and rail

content.description: Big boulder behind Hermit's Spire off the GSL Trail. Most sides are tall in chossy. Northeast corner offers bouldering potential.
